<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-11T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="344" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d344">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/516: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Acting Chairman of the American Delegation to the General
                                Disarmament Conference (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_GHS1" type="to">Gibson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-11T14:00:00-05:00">November 11, 1932—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>30. Your 36, November 9, 4 p.m. For <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_WHR1">Wilson</persName> and <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_DNH1">Norman Davis</persName>.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>I approve the arrangement requested and your understanding
                                thereof.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>I desire that at your discretion you make available in confidence
                                to <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">General McCoy</persName>
                                information which you have and may receive relating to Far Eastern
                                problems and pertinent to his problem and consideration of the
                                    <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_LERB1">Lytton</persName>
                                Report.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>Please so inform <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_MMGFR1">General
                                    McCoy</persName>.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>